<TITLE> OPA honours veteran </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 12 (bdnews24.com) -- The Old Placidians' Association (OPA) on Thursday honoured veteran teacher, Peter Shaha of St. Placid's High School, for "His Lifetime Achievement". On the occasion, at the Asian SR Hotel in Chittagong, gratitude was also extended to all who had helped make the OPA 'Fun and Fair' event, in aid of the OPA Literacy Centre, a success. At the function, Old Placidians reminisced days and events with 'Peter Shaha Sir', now 90 years old, and known as a generations' teacher. Executive committee member Opn Derrick Randolph moderated the function that was rounded off with a musical soiree.
